## Azure  steps by VM Creation
Login to Azure portal console
search the VM- Select and create a VM


Project details : Subscription --> Azure Subscription
Resources group : Development
Instance details
VM Name : Develop
Region: Central India
Availability zone : AZ
Zone options : Self selected zone
Availability zone : Zone 2, Zone 3
Security groups : Trusted launch VM
Image : select OS type : select ubuntu (Ubuntu, Windows, Linux, Redhat)
vm architecture : X64
Size : Default
Administrator account
Authentication type : SSH public key
username : azureuser
SSH public key source : generate a new key pair
SSH key type : RSA SSH format
keypair name : develop
inbound port rules
     Public inbound ports : allow selected ports
     select inbound ports : SSH 22

Disk details : default
Networking :default
Management : default 
Monitoring : default
advanced: default
tags : default
review and create 
click create


Azure connect Biaston
1. networking --> network settings --> create --> port rule--> inbound rule--> 
Destination port : 80
Name : HTTP
Click : add

2. select VM --> connect --> via Bastian -->
Authentication type: SSH private key from local file
username : azureuser
local file: pem file upload 
Open in new window : option not selected

Click connect: Terminal

sudo -i or sudo su
apt-get update
apt-get install apache2
systemctl enable apache2
systemctl service apache2
systemctl status apache2



